"title": "5329: guarantee",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5329",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A pledge given that a promise will be fulfilled; a deposit or down payment making fulfilment obligatory. All God's promises are guaranteed in and through Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Laws relating to guarantees</h2>\n<h3>Promises must be kept</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:4-Ps15:5\">PSA 15:4–15:5</a></p>\n<h3>The poor must not be oppressed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:26-Exod22:27\">EXO 22:26–22:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:10-Deut24:12\">DEU 24:10–24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17\">DEU 24:17</a></p>\n<h3>Special laws relating to women</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:3-Num30:16\">NUM 30:3–30:16</a></p>\n<h3>Guarantees could be written or spoken</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:2\">NUM 30:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:19\">EZR 10:19</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of guarantees</h2>\n<h3>Judah's pledge to bring Benjamin back</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:8-Gen43:9\">GEN 43:8–43:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen44:32\">GEN 44:32</a></p>\n<h3>The people's pledge to keep the law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:3\">2KI 23:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:32\">2CH 34:32</a></p>\n<h3>Other examples of guarantees</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:3\">JOB 17:3</a> <em>Job's need of a pledge</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:6\">JOB 22:6</a> <em>Eliphaz' accusation against Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:3\">JOB 24:3</a> <em>Job's complaint against the wicked</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:8\">EST 8:8</a> <em>the king's seal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:18\">EZK 17:18</a> <em>Zedekiah's broken pledge</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:8\">AMO 2:8</a> <em>the priests taking pledges</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:20\">MIC 7:20</a> <em>God's pledge to his people</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:21</a> <em>Baptism understood as a pledge</em></p>\n<h2>God's promises are guaranteed in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ, the guarantee of salvation for believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:22\">HEB 7:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:18-2Cor1:20\">2CO 1:18–1:20</a></p>\n<h3>The Holy Spirit, the guarantee of believers' inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:21-2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:21–1:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:13-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:5\">2CO 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Salvation guaranteed to all who believe</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16\">ROM 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:2-Rev7:3\">REV 7:2–7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:4\">REV 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:1\">REV 14:1</a></p>\n<h3>The oath of God is unbreakable</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:2\">TIT 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:17-Heb6:20\">HEB 6:17–6:20</a></p>",
